    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-11T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="486"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.20/629: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-11T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 11, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 11—3:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6337. Department’s 5504, November 4, noon, concerning announcements of arrival of
                    American troops in Liberia was promptly brought to the attention of the Foreign
                    Office. The Foreign Office now informs us that steps are being taken to prevent
                    recurrence of such incidents <pb facs="0413" n="401" xml:id="pg_401"/> which are
                    much regretted and that inquiries are being made with a view to clearing up the
                    matter. A full statement on the subject is promised at the earliest possible
                    date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
